Michelle Courtens (born 3 August 1981), performing as Michelle, is a Dutch singer, who is known from her performance in the Eurovision Song Contest 2001.
On 2 March 2001 Michelle competed in the final of the Dutch National Song Contest, with the alternative pop song "Out on My Own".
This meant she could go to the Eurovision Song Contest 2001 in Copenhagen, Denmark.
In March of that year, Out on My Own reached the 9th place in the Dutch Top 40; unique for a Eurovision song.
